what follow-up statenents given: Thank you! The reason I answered that I feel the subject is because in all the subjects we do, it doesn’t necessarily mean that we understand them all. So when a teacher is teaching, you start to select the subjects you are good at. Like if it’s mathematics you say, I understand it and if it’s chemistry you say, I understand it. So when you are about to do it and you know you understand the subject you are about to do, it makes you feel happy to do it and feel confident in yourself as well.

Translation: Maybe an example, I might come to study and the teacher goes out without me understanding anything in all the things he taught, because it may depend on a person but if I come in saying “I understand chemistry” I feel like I didn’t come to study for nothing or for no reason and that I go home with something. 
Dominik: And chemistry for example, what is it that you take home?
Student: Like if the teacher teaches us the way reactions are mixed and gives a certain solution, when I get home and they ask me what I has learned; I tell them about how when reactions are mixed it gives out other solutions.

Let’s say the teacher teaches us and gets out. If he gives out an exercise, I wouldn’t get a zero because I understand the subject he is teaching or when he teachers I retain something. So if we are given an exercise or an exam I won’t get a zero, I would succeed. That’s why.

Dominik: And you also said; another reason might be that you just love a subject.
Student: It is because we don’t understand all the subjects we study or feel like you can succeed always, but when you love a subject and say like I love mathematics even when the teacher come to teach it, you study it feeling like you love it. It’s not the same with the one that doesn’t love it.

What I meant by that was, that I loved the exercise I was doing. At times you do an exercise and feel happy depending on the subject/lesson. The subject you understand, you do it happily but the one you don’t particularly understand you are not happy to do it. That’s what I meant.

Student: Impamvu ni uko, bagenzi banjye hari ibyo bababazi ntazi. Bakarushaho kunsobanurira. Nanjye hari ibyo mba nzi, batazi nanjye nkabasobanurira.
Translation: the reason why, is because there are things my friends know/understand that I don’t know/understand. So they explain them to me even more, same as how there are things I know/understand that they don’t, so I too explain to them.

(AN): There are things that I know a lot, maybe when a parent says “if you don’t go to school, you won’t achieve anything” and I wonder why does he/she loves me while he/she didn’t study?” For example, my mom, she did not study but I wonder, there are time a parent mistreats his/her child. The parent makes tough studying and tell his/her child that if he/she doesn’t go to school, he/she won’t achieve anything and he/she won’t become a better person.  Then that is where you find a child with a lot of problems. Then whenever, I think that there are other bunch of peoples who are done with their studies and are jobless. (JN): There is a time that you do understand and get the subject. So, at that time you focus on what you understand. For example; even if I don’t understand English, it motivates me to study it because I will need it in the upcoming life but I don’t have the motivation to study Chemistry.

(JN): There is a time that you do understand and get the subject. So, at that time you focus on what you understand. For example; even if I don’t understand English, it motivates me to study it because I will need it in the upcoming life but I don’t have the motivation to study Chemistry.

(JN): When you do understand a subject, you can even answer to it.  Because when they bring questions, you fail at those questions and lose hope and motivation of studying that subject.
(DN): If you say a subject is difficult, do you basically mean you don’t understand the subject?
(JN): No, there is a time that the subject might be difficult but you want to understand it. However, you focus on that subject depends on how you want to study it.
(DN): What do you mean if you say a subject is difficult?
(JN): For instance, to answer questions in chemistry is difficult. It is also a challenge for teachers because they do not have enough materials for practice and becomes an obstacle for your learning. Then, once, we are in the national examination, they bring various questions. Same as we did for district exams, most of the questions asked were not seen in class.
(DN): Actually, we once asked two students what does it mean if a subject is difficult? One student said if a subject is difficult you just don’t understand it.  Another student said if a subject is difficult you can still understand it, you just need to put in more work. Who of the two students is right, what do you think?
(JN): The second student was right because you just need to put in more work and understand the subject.
(DN): Why do you think the second one is right?
(JN): It is because when you don’t understand a subject, you can’t come to its end and if they bring a quiz and say you don’t understand it and score a zero, no. You try your best so that you can’t score a zero, and try to succeed.
